# Post-feature quality gate (WatchFlowing)

This is a production SaaS. After **every** new feature or meaningful change, before finishing:

## Do not
- Rewrite unrelated app areas
- Delete code reserved for planned/future features
- Skip `npm run build`

## Always review

### Security
- Auth on new/changed API routes (`requireUser` / ownership checks)
- Input validation (Zod) + rate limiting on mutating/AI routes
- Prisma (no raw SQL string interpolation with user input)
- SSRF on any outbound URL fetch
- Stripe webhook signature verification (if touched)
- Telegram webhook secret verification (if touched)
- No secrets in client bundles / logs

### Performance
- Prefer `dynamic()` / lazy load for heavy or optional UI (tours, maps, chat)
- Avoid blocking LCP (defer non-critical work with idle callbacks)
- Cap probe loops and external fetches with timeouts
- Keep mobile layout and LCP goals in mind (~2.5s)

### Reliability / production
- Graceful fallbacks when DB columns or deps are missing
- User data isolation (`userId` scoping)
- Error responses without leaking internals

### Code quality
- Remove only **safe** unused imports/files from the change set
- Do not remove integration stubs or hidden UI retained for restore

## Required before done
1. `npm run build` (no TS errors)
2. Brief report: security findings, perf changes, files changed, remaining recommendations
